      <memberdef kind="function" id="class_u_tryll_node_params_base_1ab266c9fd695305c0b4388c0233942793" prot="public" static="no" const="yes" explicit="no" inline="no" virt="virtual">
        <type>TArray&lt; FString &gt;</type>
        <definition>virtual TArray&lt; FString &gt; UTryllNodeParamsBase::GetExitTargetOptions</definition>
        <argsstring>() const</argsstring>
        <name>GetExitTargetOptions</name>
        <qualifiedname>UTryllNodeParamsBase::GetExitTargetOptions</qualifiedname>
        <briefdescription>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>Dropdown options for fields tagged with FlatBuffers <computeroutput>(exit)</computeroutput>. Walks the Outer chain to find the enclosing <ref refid="struct_f_tryll_graph_description" kindref="compound">FTryllGraphDescription</ref> (typically owned by a <ref refid="class_u_tryll_workflow_asset" kindref="compound">UTryllWorkflowAsset</ref> or <ref refid="class_u_tryll_agent_component" kindref="compound">UTryllAgentComponent</ref>), then returns: [&quot;&quot;] + node names from that graph.</para>
<para>The leading empty string represents END (turn finishes after this node); Unreal&apos;s Details panel renders it as a blank entry in the dropdown.</para>
<para>Bound via UPROPERTY meta=(GetOptions=&quot;GetExitTargetOptions&quot;) on every codegen-emitted exit field. When the params UObject is not part of an editable graph (orphaned / runtime-constructed), returns just [&quot;&quot;]. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
        <inbodydescription>
        </inbodydescription>
